        {
          "weaponId": "laser_gat",
          "mount": "turret",
          "linked": 1
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Alien Megastructure",
      "desc": "Construct of unknown origin and purpose, discovered drifting in a system with no habitable worlds. Her geometry follows no human architectural tradition \u2014 angles that seem wrong, corridors that loop back on themselves, chambers that are larger on the inside than the outside. Carbon dating suggests she's older than human civilisation by orders of magnitude. She still has power. Some of her systems still respond to input. The team that activated the first one wished they hadn't.",
      "notes": "Precursor civilisation. Ancient. Incomprehensible technology. Dangerous.",
      "size": 28,
      "loco": "none",
      "toughLevel": 5,
      "armourLevel": 5,
      "speedLevel": 0,
      "handlingLevel": 0,
      "woundsLevel": 0,
      "crewLevel": 0,
      "passengers": 0,
      "mphOverride": 0,
      "mods": {},
      "weapons": [
        {
          "weaponId": "phase_weapon",
          "mount": "turret",
          "linked": 0
        },
        {
          "weaponId": "phase_weapon",
          "mount": "turret",
          "linked": 0
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Salvage Yard",
      "desc": "Orbital wrecking facility surrounded by a cloud of decommissioned vessels, failed experiments, and battle damage write-offs. She buys hulks, strips them for parts, and sells the components to anyone who doesn't ask where they came from. The yard boss knows the history of every wreck in her field and has a price for everything. The workforce is a mix of skilled engineers and desperate transients willing to cut hull plating in a vacuum for minimum wage.",
      "notes": "Ship breaking and parts trading. Surrounded by debris field. Good source of cheap equipment.",
      "size": 12,
      "loco": "none",
      "toughLevel": 0,
      "armourLevel": 0,
      "speedLevel": 0,
      "handlingLevel": 0,
      "woundsLevel": 0,
      "crewLevel": -11,
      "passengers": 0,
      "mphOverride": 0,
      "mods": {},
      "weapons": [
        {
          "weaponId": "laser_gat",
          "mount": "turret",
          "linked": 0
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Communications Relay",
      "desc": "Automated relay station that amplifies and retransmits faster-than-light communications across interstellar distances. She's unmanned most of the time \u2014 a maintenance crew visits quarterly to replace components and update software. Her destruction would cut communications between star systems, creating information blackouts that take months to repair. She's small, fragile, and strategically invaluable. Every intelligence agency in the sector has considered tapping her datastreams. Most have succeeded.",
      "notes": "Automated. Unmanned. Critical communications infrastructure. Fragile but vital.",
      "size": 6,
      "loco": "none",
      "toughLevel": -2,
      "armourLevel": -1,
      "speedLevel": 0,
      "handlingLevel": 0,
      "woundsLevel": 0,
      "crewLevel": 0,
      "passengers": 0,
      "mphOverride": 0,
      "mods": {},
      "weapons": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Ringworld Fragment",
      "desc": "Shattered section of a structure so vast that her original form would have encircled a star. What remains is a curved landscape hundreds of kilometres long, open to space on three sides and held together by materials that human science cannot replicate or even properly analyse. Atmosphere clings to her inner surface through mechanisms nobody understands, and ecosystems that evolved in isolation over millions of years produce species found nowhere else. She is simultaneously the greatest archaeological find in history and the most dangerous environment anyone has ever explored.",
      "notes": "Dyson ring fragment. Alien megastructure. Unique ecosystems. Incomprehensible scale.",
      "size": 30,
      "loco": "none",
      "toughLevel": 5,
      "armourLevel": 5,
      "speedLevel": 0,
      "handlingLevel": 0,
      "woundsLevel": 0,
      "crewLevel": 0,
      "passengers": 0,
      "mphOverride": 0,
      "mods": {},
      "weapons": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Quarantine Platform",
      "desc": "Medical isolation facility positioned far from populated stations, where patients with unknown diseases, alien biological contamination, or suspected parasitic infection are held until they're cured or dead. The medical staff are volunteers on hazard pay. The security staff are there to ensure nothing leaves. The facility has a self-destruct system that the station commander can activate without authorisation. She has never needed to use it. She checks the system every morning anyway.",
      "notes": "Medical isolation. Remote. Self-destruct capability. Staff rotate frequently.",
      "size": 12,
      "loco": "none",
      "toughLevel": 1,
      "armourLevel": 1,
      "speedLevel": 0,
      "handlingLevel": 0,
      "woundsLevel": 0,
      "crewLevel": -11,
      "passengers": 0,
      "mphOverride": 0,
      "mods": {},
